# Code Quality

When implementing (phase Code):

- Follow existing patterns in the touched directory
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones
- Keep functions focused; extract only when reused 2+ times
- Handle errors at boundaries, not every line
- Add tests only for non-trivial behavior (not getters/setters)

## File changes

- One logical change per commit when possible
- No formatting-only changes mixed with logic changes
- No commented-out code left behind
